    "client_msg_id": "CAB132E1-3B77-4C6F-A642-AED9839B818B",
    "text": "On a meta note, this question made me think about what elements of game design are “enough” to qualify as programming eg \n\n• opportunity for emergent behavior? (Conway)\n• ability to manage state / control flow?\n• System simulations (city / tycoon) - you achieve goals by modifying the environment rather than the agents \n• Has elements that can be optimized or automated \n• No single path to “win”, but some are quantitatively better than others ",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1709819831.427719",
    "parent_user_id": "UBN9AFS0N",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
